Http Protocol versions
  HTTP 1.0
  HTTP 2.1


Basic HTTP Method:
  GET
      200   OK
      
  POST
      200   OK
      201   Created
      204   No Content
  
  PUT

  
  DELETE
      200 Ok
      202 Accpted
      204 No Content
      
Http Request:
      Request URL:
      Headers
      Body
      

Http Response:
      Response Content
      Headers
      Body

Maximum POST Body Size:     Protocol never define sizes,it is left server settings that it can handle
Maximum Get Header Length:  Protocol never define sizes,it is left server settings that it can handle

Body Content:
    XML
    JSON
    HTML



Http Status Codes
      - 1xx: Informational - Request received, continuing process
          100
      - 2xx: Success - The action was successfully received,understood, and accepted
          200
          201
          203 
      - 3xx: Redirection - Further action must be taken in order to complete the request
          303
      - 4xx: Client Error - The request contains bad syntax or cannot be fulfilled
          401
      - 5xx: Server Error - The server failed to fulfill an apparently valid request
          501

Http Request Payload/Message Content Type:

Http Content Types:

Link Definition:
A link can be viewed as a statement of the form "{context IRI} has a  {relation type} resource at {target IRI}, which has {target attributes}".
The Link entity-header field provides a means for serialising one or more links in HTTP headers
 
 References:
    HTTP 1.1 RFC: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2616#section-7
  
 
